instructions: OVEN: Preheat the oven to 400°F (205°C). Remove the tray from the box. Leave the film on the tray; do not open it. Place the tray on a baking sheet. Bake frozen for about 35 to 40 minutes. Remove the plastic wrap and continue baking for 10 to 15 minutes. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then enjoy. Please note that cooking times may vary depending on the type of oven. For food safety and quality, cook to a minimum internal temperature of 160°F (71°C). MICROWAVE: Remove the tray from the box. Leave the plastic wrap on the tray; do not open it. Cook on high for about 15 minutes. Remove the plastic wrap and continue cooking on 50% (medium) for an additional 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then enjoy. Please note that cooking time may vary depending on the type of oven. For safety and food quality reasons, cook to a minimum internal temperature of 71°C.
